    introduction: "I pray for you that your life reflects reverence towards God in all your public speeches and secret actions in the name of Jesus, Amen. Make your life a testament to God’s glory like Joseph. He made his life continually seeking to honour God. He did not sleep with his master’s wife, despite the pressure and persuasion by the woman. He forgave his brothers, even though they sold him into slavery and denied him of his father’s inheritance. He did not look for Potiphar, after he became the prime minister in Egypt, to punish him or visit vengeance upon him for wrongfully accusing him and sending him to prison. Joseph’s habit, ideas, actions and thoughts, reverenced God. The word “reverence” means honour, or respect felt or shown to somebody. Joseph also had a deep reverence to hierarchy, authority and the Almighty God. Gen. 39:9 refers, “There is none greater in this honour than I”. Thus speaks of reverence for hierarchy. Joseph respected his position as an overseer in Potiphar’s house. He didn’t abuse that privilege. Let somebody, learn something here. Until your life becomes a symbol of reverence to God, you will not become a point or person of reference in life. A person of reference is someone whose life is worthy of emulation. He is an example who enjoys public commendation and recommendation. He will be a person respected or held in high esteem by others.",
    prayer_focus: "O God, give me the grace to reverence you all the time.",
