    introduction: "May your presence in a position of influence bring joy to your people and those around the neighbourhood in the name of Jesus, Amen. Continuing the running story on Joseph in previous days, we see that Joseph loved righteousness and hated wickedness. That’s why God anointed him with oil of gladness above his fellow workers in Potiphar’s house (Psalm 45:7 refers). Those who carry the oil of gladness don’t inflict people with sadness. This is the reason Joseph was a channel of joy, success, flourishing and prosperity. When his master realized this, he handed everything he had except his wife, into the care and custody of Joseph. Something more to note of is that Joseph reverenced the authority of his master and lived in that house with all sincerity and without hypocrisy. If he had lived in hypocrisy Joseph would have been having secret love affair with his master’s wife without his master knowing. You know, since madam was the one that initiated it, she would have carefully covered it up but Joseph wouldn’t go far and madam would not let him go anywhere. In the process Joseph would have lost his destiny. Many men and women, young and old have lost their destinies in this manner. May God help somebody in this situation to opt out in Jesus name, Amen.",
