    introduction: "May your life be such that you can be trusted with things without fear of loss, misuse or diversion to wrong use. May your life simply showcase integrity. Integrity speaks of transparency and no hypocrisy. Integrity is having a changeless character in secret or in public. You are who you are even when no one is watching you. This was the portrait of Joseph. I pray it should be yours and mine too. When God trusts you, He can entrust things or gifts to you and compel people to entrust their assets and resources to you, to take care for them; without probing you. God created Joseph into a person who will have reverence for integrity. That’s why He gave him two powerful dreams on trust (Gen. 37:5-10) and entrusted him with the responsibility of interpreting dreams to all classes of people. What has God entrusted you with? What gifting has He entrusted you with that you need to keep with integrity? You see, Gehazi would have been someone with a double portion of Elisha’s anointing, but Gehazi lost it, because he didn’t have reverence for integrity (2 Kings 5:22-26). He told lies to his master and took things from people against the master’s permission or instruction.",
